1.1 Solr index (demo password required)
* [SOLR Indexer Status&gt;http://current.dev.curriki.org/solr/indexer/status] (from there you can click on a recently indexed document, see its indexed view (click (indexed), and see the analysis result of each field)
* [SOLR Indexer update&gt;http://current.dev.curriki.org/solr/indexer/update] (use with care!)
* [SOLR Itas&gt; http://current.dev.curriki.org/solr/itas] (full query, developer results)
* [SOLR admin&gt;http://current.dev.curriki.org/solr/admin/] (for statistics, view configurations, test analysis)
* [indexed view of a document (curriki help here)&gt;http://current.dev.curriki.org/solr/indexer/indexed?doc=Coll_curriki.CurrikiHelp] to compare to its [itas view of CurrikiHelp&gt;http://current.dev.curriki.org/itas?q=%7B%21lucene%7D+fullname%3AColl_curriki.CurrikiHelp]

